Package <Unnamed>

Interface Summary
Grid<E> Grid provides an interface for a two-dimensional, grid-like environment containing arbitrary objects.
 

Class Summary
AbstractGrid<E> AbstractGrid contains the methods that are common to grid implementations.
Bishop A Bishop is a chess piece that can only move diagonally but as many spaces as possible.
Board Board represesents a rectangular game board, containing Piece objects.
BoardDisplay BoardDisplay is used to display the contents of a game board.
BoundedGrid<E> A BoundedGrid is a rectangular grid with a finite number of rows and columns.
Game Game oversees the match of chess.
HumanPlayer HumanPlayer is a player that is controlled by the user instead of the computer.
King A King chess piece can move one adjacent space or one diagonal space.
Knight A Knight is a chess piece that moves in an L-shape fashion.
Location A Location object represents the row and column of a location in a two-dimensional grid.
Move Represents a single move, in which a piece moves to a destination location.
Pawn A Pawn piece can move forward one space or two spaces if it has not moved yet.
Piece A Piece is an object that can be placed on the chess board.
Player Abstract class Player focuses on its board, name, and color.
Queen A Queen piece can move as many possible spaces in any direction.
RandomPlayer RandomPlayer is controlled solely by the computer and always makes a random but valid move.
Rook A Rook piece can move as many possible spaces directly forwards, backwards, or to the sides.
SmartPlayer SmartPlayer evaluates possible moves of both itself and its opponent in order to make the best move for itself.
